1.title: From School Bus to Cool Bus
1.plot: YouTube sensation Logan Paul purchased an old school bus with the intention of traveling the United States to meet his fans. So he turned to WCC for help. A crazy exterior and zen interior take it from School to Cool.

2.title: WCC's Pumping Iron
2.plot: Gunner Peterson, trainer to the stars needs a mobile gym for a big challenge, getting former football star Jarred Lorenzen back in shape. But this can't be any old gym on wheels, and it's up to the team at West Coast Customs to deliver.

3.title: Rollin' in my 5.0
3.plot: Andy Campanaro commissioned WCC to build a purple 1968 Mustang convertible for his wife's 50th birthday. And now it's her turn to surprise her husband, with his dream Mustang, a 90's 5.0, West Coast Customs-style.

4.title: Green Day's Bookmobile Tour Bus
4.plot: Green Day was coming up, they toured the nation in an old bookmobile customized by Tre Cool's dad. Now it's rusting away. Now, they are partnering up with Wheels for Wishes to bring the bookmobile back to it's former touring glory.

5.title: Black Panter Lexus
5.plot: After the success of the Sriracha car, Lexus wants WCC to build a Black Panther inspired car to showcase their LC-500. Big, aggressive, wild and powered by Vibranium. This will be a car fit for the King of Wakanda.

6.title: SEMA Neckbreakers
6.plot: With the release of the new Stinger, Kia asks WCC to design a vehicle that will turn heads at the SEMA Show in Las Vegas; the car company also has a luxurious Cadenza that they want taken to the next level to show the world that Kia is all grown up.

7.title: El Dorado Seville
7.plot: Chiropractor KenGee Erlich finally found his dream car, a '57 El Dorado Seville and now it's time for WCC to give this car a fresh new look. Now when he cruises down the street everyone will know that the doctor is in.

8.title: Joe Jonas Falcon
8.plot: Pop sensation Joe Jonas loves vintage cars. And his new baby is a '64 Ford Falcon. Now he's brought the car to West Coast Customs to bring it back to life. The team will give this car a full overhaul to give Joe a car as smooth and silky as his voice.

9.title: The Continental Camaro
9.plot: Continental Tires wants a vehicle that will stand out from the crowd, so they've reached out to their longtime partners at West Coast Customs for help. Partnering with Petty's Garage they'll transform a '69 Camaro into a wow Camaro.

10.title: Ultimate Rescue Truck
10.plot: When Jake Paul saw the Cool Bus that his brother Logan had made at WCC, he knew he needed some bigger and better. After experiencing post-hurricane Houston, he wants the team at WCC to build a merch truck that doubles as the ultimate rescue truck.

1.title: Virgin Gaming
1.plot: With the launch of the new Virgin Gaming site premiering at E3, Sir Richard Branson teams up with West Coast Customs to transform an armored vehicle into a luxurious gamers lounge.

2.title: Alienware
2.plot: A Hummer is known for it's superior off road performance, but after West Coast Customs is done with it, this Hummer will be known as the ultimate PC gamers vehicle at Comic Con.

3.title: OX-Baja or Bust
3.plot: Jeff "Ox" Kargola turns out insane tricks on his motorbike, but now West Coast Customs will trick out his truck as they race to the finish line just in time for the Baja 1000.

4.title: Spy Optics
4.plot: Looking good and doing it in style is what West Coast Customs and Spy Optics are known for, now Ryan and his team turn an RV fit for a grandma into a VIP lounge fit for pro snowboarder Louie Vito.

5.title: Monster Energy
5.plot: Jonathan Davis, lead singer of Korn has been mashing up music for years with his NuMetal style, now West Coast Customs is given the challenge to mix things up with a 69 Camaro body on top of a 2008 GTO.

6.title: Techno Denali
6.plot: Two world wide brands Hewlett Packard and West Coast Customs collaborate to turn an ordinary Denali into a mobile multimedia platform with all the latest HP technology.

7.title: Juiceblendz-Smooth Operator
7.plot: This tired RV is not the only thing to transform into a smoothie making machine, Ryan gets inspired by the build and restarts his healthy living and shares it with others.

8.title: Monster Cable Tron-This Is Not a Game
8.plot: West Coast Customs steps into the future by transforming and Audi R8 into a Tron inspired super car to be unveiled at CES.

9.title: Best Buy/Discovery-Hot Dog Hero
9.plot: The team decks out a sizzlin' hot-dog cart and surprises a heroic food vendor who stood watch outside the Discovery Channel headquarters during a life threatening hostage crisis.

10.title: Rascal Flatts-Take the T-Tops Out
10.plot: "Take the T-tops out" and that is exactly what Ryan and the crew do when they team up with Rascal Flatts for the release of their single "Red Camaro"

1.title: Gwynn's Legacy Mustang
1.plot: West Coast Customs is honoring the man whose determination and strength of spirit has helped so many. Taking design cues from Darrell's last winning dragster, the WCC team will transform a brand new Mustang into the ultimate tribute car.

2.title: Will.I.Am of the Black Eyed Peas
2.plot: This is the fusion of a classic 1958 Corvette with the modern amenities of an '08 Vette, conceptualized by celebrity producer and hip-hop artist, Will.i.am. This may be one of the most complicated builds WCC has ever encountered.

3.title: 7 Step Fiesta
3.plot: The team at WCC has joined forces with Best Buy and Ford to create the ultimate example of the "7 steps to customize your car." Best Buy provides the platform, Ford hooks us up with a new Fiesta and West Coast Customs injects the whole thing with a heavy dose of incredible.

4.title: Zippo Jeep
4.plot: Zippo and Jeep, come together to form the king of all camping customs. With classic styling cues provided by Jeep's time honored design, paired with Zippo's distinctly American characteristics, this build promises to get you outdoors.

5.title: Mark's Mobile Office
5.plot: The modern star needs some way to stay connected at all times. Get ready for a chariot fit for a Rock Star, ready to brave The Perfect Storm and cruise into Boogie Nights. This is Mark Wahlberg's Cadillac, the most connected SUV on Earth.

6.title: Bieber's Bling
6.plot: One of the brightest young stars gracing today's celebrity sky is Justin Bieber. But amidst all of his star power one thing is missing - the perfect car. With the help of WCC, Justin is soon to be the owner of the ultimate Cadillac CTS-V.

7.title: Kustom Karts
7.plot: Nintendo and WCC have come together to bring two icons of the gaming world to life. Starting with a couple of factory GEMS, the team at WCC will get to work building the first real world incarnation of the Nintendo's Mario Karts.

8.title: Monster Week
8.plot:

9.title: DC Tundra
9.plot: DC Shoes and West Coast Customs create the ultimate motocross support vehicle. Using a Toyota Tundra as their canvas, the WCC crew gets to work outfitting this rugged and mean masterpiece with all the essentials for off-road domination.

10.title: Operation Camaro
10.plot: Operation Mend's aim is to provide severely wounded soldiers with the specialized treatments they require to re-enter society comfortably. With a 2011 Camaro as their platform - the crew is prepared to create the incredible as a thank you.

11.title: Double Play
11.plot: Kia and WCC are working together to create a pair of sports-themed rides for Blake Griffin and Michelle Wei- complete with pop-up gaming stations in their respective trunks and jaw-dropping custom touches throughout.

12.title: The SEMA Experience
12.plot: CEO and creative force behind the World Famous West Coast Customs, Ryan Friedlinghaus, will take you behind the scenes at the largest aftermarket car show on Earth. From the newest trends to the coolest cars, this is the SEMA experience.

13.title: Micro-Stang
13.plot: Microsoft and WCC team up on a new build. A '67 fastback body on a 2012 chassis giving it that classic look with all the modern conveniences. These two powerhouses create the most technologically advanced ride on the planet.

14.title: Camaro for a Cause
14.plot: WCC and the American Cancer Society join forces to build a 2011 Camaro. This'll be the one slick creation to be auctioned off at the Cattle Baron's Ball. And with all the proceeds going to the Society, this truly is a Camaro for a cause.

15.title: Family Affair
15.plot: It's family time at West Coast Customs. First, Ryan turns a Mercedes Sprinter into the office. Then wife Meagan designs a special-edition Fiat. Even Ryan's son Dylan gets into the act by helping Dad design a new Trophy Truck.

16.title: Vader's Ride
16.plot: The Force is strong with Ryan on this one. Lucas Films has asked WCC to build Darth Vadar's ride, and it's a dream job for this Star Wars fan. Ryan channels his inner Jedi to come up with a car that will please even the Dark Lord himself.

1.title: Shaq's Back
1.plot: It's a blast from the past when Shaquille O'Neal asks Ryan to build him a new car. After many years and countless cars, Shaq's back wants a Jeep.. But it's gotta be extra large. So the team take a four door Wrangle and super-size it.

2.title: West Coast Customs Joins the Military
2.plot: Ryan gets a call from the Marines to build a mini West Coast Customs at Camp Pendleton. In addition the Marines want Ryan and his crew to customize a 2012 Chevy Silverado to be given away to one lucky Marine at the grand opening.

3.title: Skype-Stream
3.plot: When Skype call on WCC to create a Skype lounge, great things happen. Watch as Ryan and the boys get out the can opener to turn an ordinary Airstream into "Skype-Stream".

4.title: Firefall
4.plot: The West Coast Customs crew is no stranger to creating insane gaming vehicles. But nothing can prepare them for their biggest challenge yet as they modify a tour bus to match the beautifully devastating vision of the Firefall gaming world.

5.title: Geek Squad
5.plot: West Coast Customs Geek out at NASCAR when Carl Edwards asks Ryan to design a wrap for his race car that's more chic and less geek. Best Buy loves the design so much, they also ask the WCC crew to un-geekify a VW Geekmobile.

1.title: Too Hot to Handle
1.plot: Lexus and Sriracha are teaming up and they want Ryan to build them a spicy Lexus IS. Ryan thinks it's going to be an easy job - Sriracha colored paint and a pepper-filled steering wheel. But it's never easy creating one of a kind masterpieces. And to add fuel to the fire, boxing legend Oscar de la Hoya wants his new Lamborghini Aventador wrapped in matte satin. The heat is getting turned up at West Coast Customs.

2.title: Mad Dash to SEMA
2.plot: SEMA is the Superbowl for the car world. A huge four day event held in Las Vegas with everyone who's anyone from the car world attending. A lot of vendors have large booths, but none bigger than West Coast Customs. But instead of just showing off their work, they put the attendee's of SEMA to work, taking classes and learning from the experts at West Coast Customs in areas such as paint, wrap, interior, fabrication and electronics. But before the team can even make it to Vegas, BendPak drops a job in his lap. They want him to build a Raptor, Mustang and trailer for ...

3.title: A Wild Ride
3.plot: The marketing team at Kmart want to create a mobile experience for the entire family using virtual reality that can travel to Kmart's across the country. They're not quite sure what they want, but they know they want something cool, so of course they head over to West Coast Customs, the creators of cool. Now the WCC team is focused on building a state of the art virtual reality bus that can hit the road and make a splash. The first stop is an event at St. Jude Children's Hospital. So Ryan and the team are working overtime so these kids can have a one of a kind ...

6.title: Post Malone's Old Skool Explorer
6.plot: Hip-Hop artist Post Malone is in the shop to view a new music video that he made with Ryan's young son Dylan. While there, he tells Ryan he's always dreamed of having a Texas Slab, and he wants Ryan and the team to create it. Post likes things retro, so for this build we're going back to the style that originally made WCC famous. It's time to make a pimped out 1991 Explorer, complete with 26" wheels, lambo doors, and whatever old school features Ryan can come up with. It's time to see if West Coast Customs still has it's old school chops.

7.title: Mitsubishi reModel A
7.plot: One hundred years ago Mitsubishi Motors built the first mass produced car in Japan, the Mitsubishi Model-A. For Mitsubishi's 100th anniversary they want to bring back the past and marry it with the future. And there's no better place for that to happen than West Coast Customs. Ryan and his team will take viewers back in time by recreating the original Model-A. And to bring this vehicle into the modern age, they will put the body on top of a Mitsubishi PHEV a plug-in SUV. With an interior of today and an exterior of yesterday this car will truly be a celebration of ...

imdb.title: Inside West Coast Customs
plot: Inside the world famous "west coast customs" Ryan Friedlinghaus presents some of the dopest transformations on some of the dopest vehicles, with some high end clientele, Ryan and the west coast customs team don't disappoint!::Jason Connop
